<!DOCTYPE Test SYSTEM '../../../../../../../../../../test.dtd'>
<Test
    ID="getDeclaredClasses1010"
    date-of-creation="2005-7-01"
    timeout="1"
    >
        
        
        <APITestDescription>
            <TestedClass name="java.lang.Class"/>
            <TestedMethod name="public Class[] getDeclaredClasses() throws SecurityException"/>
            <Description>
The test is against the getDeclaredClasses1010 method.

The test performs the following checks on the method.
1) The method returns an array of length 0 
   if the Class object has no member classes or interfaces. 
2) Returns an array containing Class objects representing all the classes and interfaces 
   that are members of the class represented by this Class object
   if this Class object has no super-class. 
3) Returns an array containing Class objects representing all the classes and interfaces 
   that are members of the class represented by this Class object
   but excuded class and interface members inherited from superclasses.
            </Description>
            </APITestDescription>
        <Source name="getDeclaredClasses1010.java"/>
        <Runner ID="Runtime">
            <Param name="toRun" value="org.apache.harmony.test.func.api.java.lang.F_Class_getDeclaredClasses1010.getDeclaredClasses1010"/>
        </Runner>
</Test>
